'''[[Bhutan]]''' have participated in the [[ABU Radio Song Festival]] once. The Bhutanese broadcaster, Centennial Radio, has been the organiser of the Bhutanese entry since the country's debut in the contest in [[ABU Radio Song Festival 2012|2012]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ABU Radio Song Festival website showcases a strong field of entries|url=http://www.abu.org.my/Latest_News-@-ABU_Radio_Song_Festival_website_showcases_a_strong_field_of_entries.aspx|publisher=Asia-Pacific Broadcasting Union|accessdate=17 August 2012|date=3 August 2012}}</ref><ref name="ABU Radio">{{cite web|last=Mikheev|first=Andy|title=ABU Radio Song Festival 2012 Participants|url=http://esckaz.com/2012/abu_radio.htm|publisher=ESCKaz|accessdate=4 October 2012|date=4 October 2012}}</ref>

==History==
===2012===
Centennial Radio is one of the founder members in the ABU Radio Song Festivals, having participated in the very first [[ABU Radio Song Festival 2012]].<ref name="ABU Radio"/> At the first festival two songs were submitted to participate in the event, Dechen Wangmo was selected to participate in the final while Sonam Tshewang was not selected by the panel at the ABU. In Seoul Dechen finished in 6th place.

===2014===
On 30 December 2013 Centennial Radio confirmed to Eurovoix.com that Bhutan would not participate in the ABU Radio Song Festival 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Bhutan: Will Not Take Part In The ABU Radio Song Festival 2014|url=http://eurovoix.com/2013/12/30/bhutan-will-not-take-part-in-the-abu-radio-song-festival-2014/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref>

